  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To establish six joint cassava farms at parish level and group level as a social enterprise. The women will then be trained in modern methods of farming. The women will also be given business skills and financial management training. The various groups will also be trained on how to manage savings groups to enable the members build the habit of savings and also serve as a source of acquiring loans to set up or expand their business. Many of the women are living with HIV and many of them were in Internally Displaced Camps. The project will also undertake HIV education in the project area.It is expected that 84 women, 100 girls and 100 boys will benefit from the project</narrative>
